….Quartet Stripped Over Chijindu Ujah’s Doping Violation ABUJA – The Anti-Doping Division of the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS ADD) has stripped the Team GB of the 4×100m relay silver medal it won at the Tokyo summer Olympics following Doping Violation by its lead runner, Chijindu ‘CJ’ Ujah. The Athlete (Ujah) was found to have committed an Anti-Doping Rule Violation (ADRV) pursuant to Article 2.1 of the IOC Anti-Doping Rules (IOC ADR) and consequently disqualified in the 4×100 m relay final and 100m sprints. CSOs: Buhari’s Delay In Assenting To Electoral Act… Police Not To Blame For Fatal Accident In Ihiala -Anambra CP The decision also means a forfeiture of the medals, diplomas, points and prizes he won at the games, together with the relay quartet, in accordance with Article 10.1 of the IOC Anti-Doping Rules for the Tokyo Olympic Games 2020. The decision would mean that Zharnel Hughes, Richard Kilty and Nethaneel Mitchell-Blake would be stripped of their silver medals while the Canadian Team takes the silver and China upgraded to the bronze medal. CAS also requested the World Athletics (WA) to “consider any further action within its own jurisdiction and pursuant to its own Rules including the determination of any period of ineligibility. Following the in-competition Doping control test after the Final of the 4x100m sprint relay, the Athlete returned an Adverse Analytical Finding (AAF) from his samples for the prohibited substances enobosarm (ostarine) and S-23, Selective Androgen Receptor Modulators (SARMS) which are prohibited by WADA at all times. On 12 August 2021, the International Testing Agency (ITA), acting on behalf of the IOC, formally notifiedthe Athlete of the AAF and he was provisionally suspended by the Athletics Integrity Unit (AIU). POLL The B-sample analysis requested by the Athlete also confirmed the A-sample analysis and the ITA referred the matter to the CAS ADD for determination on the ADRV and the imposition of sanctions.